Could I have a blanket?

69
00:22:03,061 --> 00:22:09,314
- A blanket!
- Too late. Tomorrow.

70
00:22:09,485 --> 00:22:16,734
He'll be here tomorrow, I think.
Goodnight.

71
00:22:51,696 --> 00:22:55,944
- Can you speak English?
- Your cell is open.

72
00:22:56,118 --> 00:23:00,495
Blankets, three cells down.
You get me one.

73
00:24:18,665 --> 00:24:21,203
I needed a blanket.

74
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:27,214
William Hayes.

75
00:24:42,524 --> 00:24:45,692
I needed a blanket, I was cold!

76
00:26:01,150 --> 00:26:03,558
Jesus...

77
00:26:03,736 --> 00:26:06,986
Come on, you must stand.

78
00:26:08,031 --> 00:26:11,946
You'd better walk around,
or your feet will swell up.

79
00:26:12,119 --> 00:26:19,287
- You've got to be crazy.
- We all are. Smoke some of this.

80
00:26:20,171 --> 00:26:26,755
You've been out for days,
talking all kinds of shit.

81
00:26:26,928 --> 00:26:30,463
