before we got your letter.

152
00:34:18,225 --> 00:34:21,428
She's saving to come back here...

153
00:34:21,603 --> 00:34:27,273
Don't let her come.
How's Rob? How's Peg?

154
00:34:27,443 --> 00:34:30,728
They're the same. You know.

155
00:34:30,904 --> 00:34:36,113
We told the neighbours
you were in hospital in Europe.

156
00:34:36,286 --> 00:34:42,788
This is Stanley Daniels.
He's the American Consul here.

157
00:34:42,959 --> 00:34:50,754
Billy, we're going to do everything
in our power to get you out of here.

158
00:34:50,926 --> 00:34:57,843
Thas Necdit Yesil,
the lawyer you asked for.

159
00:34:58,017 --> 00:35:02,182
I know exactly what you feel,
but you must not worry.

160
00:35:02,356 --> 00:35:06,567
We'll get the right court
and the right judge.

161
00:35:06,735 --> 00:35:10,187
I'll arrange everything, just right.

162
00:35:11,615 --> 00:35:18,032
I understand that if you get bail,
is easy to get across the border.

163
00:35:18,205 --> 00:35:24,575
Thas what we're shooting for.
I've spoken to the State Department.

164
00:35:24,753 --> 00:35:30,045
Right now, relations with the Turks
aren't too good. Nixon upset them.

165
00:35:30,218 --> 00:35:36,507
- Our best bet is right here.
- Dad, I'll pay you back for this.

166
00:35:36,684 --> 00:35:41,062
Money doesn't matter, Billy.
Not at this stage.

167
00:35:46,986 --> 00:35:53,026
- Where did you get that limp?
- I twisted my ankle.

168
00:35:53,202 --> 00:35:58,195
- Where are you staying?
- The Hilton.

169
00:35:58,374 --> 00:36:03,879
- How do you like Istanbul?
- Interesting place.

170
00:36:04,046 --> 00:36:09,504
The food is lousy. The crap
they sell in the restaurants...

171
00:36:09,678 --> 00:36:14,885
I had to run to the toilet.
You should have seen the toilet.

172
00:36:15,058 --> 00:36:22,437
I'll eat at the Hilton every night.
Steak, French fries and ketchup.

173
00:36:29,823 --> 00:36:32,990
Billy...

174
00:36:33,161 --> 00:36:39,496
- Why did you do it?
- Money.

175
00:36:40,752 --> 00:36:44,501
I know you kids smoke that stuff
and we drink booze, -

176
00:36:44,673 --> 00:36:48,968
- but taking it across the border,
thas stupid.

177
00:36:49,137 --> 00:36:51,591
I know.

178
00:36:51,764 --> 00:36:57,601
Dad... get me out of here.

179
00:36:57,771 --> 00:37:02,599
I promise you. Just sit tight.

180
00:37:02,777 --> 00:37:07,687
Let me work with Mr. Daniels
and Mr. Yesil here.

181
00:37:07,865 --> 00:37:11,115
We'll get you out, okay?

182
00:37:11,285 --> 00:37:15,235
Hey, Billy... Okay?

183
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,456
Okay.

184
00:39:01,236 --> 00:39:05,733
- What did that prosecutor say?
- Is not important.

185
00:39:05,908 --> 00:39:11,247
We made our case. You spoke well.
The judge liked you.

186
00:39:30,267 --> 00:39:34,051
Mr. Hayes, the judge is coming back.

187
00:40:16,399 --> 00:40:20,446
- Four years, two months.
- Four years?

188
00:40:20,613 --> 00:40:22,689
We'll appeal.

189
00:40:22,865 --> 00:40:28,951
Ill be reduced for good behaviour.
It is only for possession.

190
00:40:29,122 --> 00:40:33,998
The prosecutor wanted
a life sentence for smuggling.

191
00:40:34,169 --> 00:40:39,709
To be honest, Mr. Hayes,
it is a great victory.

192
00:40:50,062 --> 00:40:56,479
With good time,
it works out to about three years.

193
00:40:56,652 --> 00:40:59,819
And then there's the appeal.

194
00:40:59,989 --> 00:41:08,412
Daniels and Yesil
are all working for you.

195
00:41:08,581 --> 00:41:12,365
We're trying to get you transferred.

196
00:41:12,543 --> 00:41:18,416
Daniels thinks there might be
a political amnesty any month now.

197
00:41:22,054 --> 00:41:25,969
All right, Billy...

198
00:41:26,142 --> 00:41:31,812
I know it sounds tough,
but we are going to get you out.

199
00:41:31,980 --> 00:41:37,320
I promise you.
Don't do anything stupid.

200
00:41:37,486 --> 00:41:41,188
They could play with your sentence.

201
00:41:42,993 --> 00:41:46,197
All right, now...

202
00:41:48,750 --> 00:41:55,168
I'm putting $500 in the bank.
Anything you need, you write.

203
00:41:55,340 --> 00:42:00,547
There's food here,
candy, writing paper, -

204
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:08,052
- books, cigarettes, soap,
toothbrush...

205
00:42:13,442 --> 00:42:16,562
I've sold insurance for 30 years.

206
00:42:16,737 --> 00:42:20,356
Now I've got to see my own son...

207
00:42:20,533 --> 00:42:25,076
Jesus!

208
00:42:28,917 --> 00:42:36,000
If I could be where you are...
I'd be there.

209
00:42:38,760 --> 00:42:42,379
I love you, Dad.

210
00:43:12,130 --> 00:43:16,627
You take good care of my boy,
or I'll have your fucking head!

211
00:44:49,610 --> 00:44:55,779
Dear Susan,
1970 has now passed into 1971.

212
00:44:55,949 --> 00:44:59,948
You can drift in here
and never know you're gone.

213
00:45:00,122 --> 00:45:06,373
You can fade so far out, you
don't know where you are anymore.

214
00:45:06,544 --> 00:45:14,969
I find loneliness is a physical pain
that hurts all over.

215
00:45:46,378 --> 00:45:49,664
To the Turks
everything is "soyle boyle".

216
00:45:49,840 --> 00:45:53,792
It means "like this, like that."
You never know what will happen.

217
00:45:55,556 --> 00:45:59,885
All foreigners are "ayip."
They're considered dirty.

218
00:46:00,060 --> 00:46:05,221
So is homosexuality, but they
do it every chance they get.

219
00:46:05,399 --> 00:46:10,027
There are about 1,000 things
that are "ayip".

220
00:46:10,197 --> 00:46:15,439
