01:36:47,494 --> 01:36:53,081
I studied philosophy at Harvard,
and also at Oxford.

479
01:36:53,249 --> 01:36:58,375
I also studied in Vienna,
and now I study here.

480
01:36:58,547 --> 01:37:03,256
They put me here.
They say I raped a little child.

481
01:37:03,428 --> 01:37:07,805
They'll never let me go.
They won't let you go, either.

482
01:37:07,973 --> 01:37:13,763
They tell you they'll let you go,
but in fact you stay.

483
01:37:13,938 --> 01:37:19,609
You see, we all of us
come from a factory.

484
01:37:19,778 --> 01:37:24,737
Sometimes the factory makes
bad machines that don't work.

485
01:37:24,908 --> 01:37:29,405
The bad machines
don't know they're bad machines.

486
01:37:29,580 --> 01:37:36,829
But the factory knows you are one
of the machines that doesn't work.

487
01:37:37,005 --> 01:37:41,668
I think we've spoken enough
for today.

488
01:37:41,844 --> 01:37:44,679
I wish you goodnight.

489
01:39:27,123 --> 01:39:30,207
My God!

490
01:39:34,922 --> 01:39:36,963
Billy!

491
01:39:40,721 --> 01:39:44,968
What have they done to you?

492
01:39:49,522 --> 01:39:53,140
Your family is fine.

493
01:39:55,988 --> 01:40:00,696
Senator Buckley has made
a special plea on your behalf.

494
01:40:00,867 --> 01:40:05,577
They've called you a pawn in the
game between Nixon and the Turks.

495
01:40:05,748 --> 01:40:10,042
The letters are coming in.
People do care.

496
01:40:16,967 --> 01:40:20,633
What?

497
01:40:20,805 --> 01:40:23,379
Take it off.

498
01:40:23,558 --> 01:40:30,973
- You'll just make yourself...
- Take it off.

499
01:40:34,319 --> 01:40:36,858
S'il vous plait.

500
01:41:10,400 --> 01:41:14,480
Billy...

501
01:41:16,574 --> 01:41:23,111
I wish I could make it better
for you. Please, don't.

502
01:41:25,374 --> 01:41:28,044
Don't.

503
01:41:42,393 --> 01:41:47,351
- Susan.
- Yes, Billy.

504
01:41:47,523 --> 01:41:51,438
I love you.

505
01:41:55,866 --> 01:41:59,401
I love you.

506
01:42:07,128 --> 01:42:10,746
Your father gave me this for you.

507
01:42:10,923 --> 01:42:15,918
There's pictures of your mom
and dad, and Rob and Peg.

508
01:42:16,095 --> 01:42:21,850
And in the back there's a picture
of your old friend Mr. Franklin.

509
01:42:23,187 --> 01:42:26,602
Remember him? From the bank.

510
01:42:28,358 --> 01:42:33,270
He's over in Greece now.
He bought a ticket.

511
01:42:36,242 --> 01:42:41,699
I'll give it to them for you.

512
01:42:41,874 --> 01:42:47,663
Don't count on them.
Don't count on anyone but yourself.

513
01:42:56,514 --> 01:43:00,975
You're running out of time.
If you stay here, you'll die.

514
01:43:01,144 --> 01:43:07,349
You've got to get yourself together.
You've got to get out of here.

515
01:44:47,884 --> 01:44:51,467
Good morning, my American friend.

516
01:44:51,639 --> 01:44:56,347
There will be trouble
if you go this way.

517
01:44:56,517 --> 01:45:00,563
A good Turk
always walks to the right.

518
01:45:00,730 --> 01:45:05,559
Left is Communist.
Right is good.

519
01:45:08,530 --> 01:45:13,323
You must go the other way.

520
01:45:13,494 --> 01:45:16,863
The other way is good.

521
01:45:19,292 --> 01:45:23,372
Where are you going?
Why don't you walk the wheel?

522
01:45:23,546 --> 01:45:28,375
What is the matter,
my American friend?

523
01:45:32,473 --> 01:45:36,422
A bad machine
doesn't know he's a bad machine.

524
01:45:36,601 --> 01:45:42,475
You still don't believe
you're a bad machine?

525
01:45:42,650 --> 01:45:45,770
To know yourself is to know God.

526
01:45:45,945 --> 01:45:50,655
The factory knows,
thas why they put you here.

527
01:45:50,826 --> 01:45:56,865
- In time you'll know.
- I already know.

528
01:45:57,041 --> 01:46:02,996
You are a bad machine, thas why
the factory keeps you here.

529
01:46:03,172 --> 01:46:06,090
Do you know how I know?

530
01:46:06,259 --> 01:46:11,052
I know because I'm from the factory.

531
01:46:11,223 --> 01:46:14,259
I make the machines.

532
01:48:48,891 --> 01:48:53,020
Max.

533
01:48:55,107 --> 01:48:58,108
Max!

534
01:49:02,240 --> 01:49:08,907
I'm going away.
I've come to say goodbye.

535
01:49:10,623 --> 01:49:15,831
You see, if I stay here,
I'm going to die.

536
01:49:16,004 --> 01:49:20,714
You'll die. Don't die, Max.

537
01:49:20,885 --> 01:49:24,752
Please, don't die.

538
01:49:24,930 --> 01:49:28,430
I'm going to come back for you.

539
01:49:28,601 --> 01:49:32,849
You hang on for me.

540
01:51:28,104 --> 01:51:33,644
You're not taking me
to the sanatorium!

